# --- Security hardening (added 2026-04-18) ---
# Never commit credentials, secrets, or key files under any circumstances.
# If you need to store secrets locally, put them in the quarantine folder:
#   E:\TY-Ecosystem\_SECRETS_DO_NOT_COMMIT\
# or use a password manager. Never place them inside any repo.

# Plaintext key/secret notes (the specific incident pattern)
book/key.txt
book/key 1.txt
book/key*.txt
**/key.txt
**/key*.txt

# Credential file patterns (general protection)
**/*.secret
**/*.secrets
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/credentials
**/credentials.*

# Environment files
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.sample
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Editor and OS artifacts (minor hygiene)
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
~$*